title: For Sale:  Armalite AR50 .50BMG
postcontent:
As the title says, Armalite AR-50.  One of the most accurate .50BMG rifles available.  It will shoot sub MOA in the right hands, which are not mine.  I got it in trade with a Bushnell 10X scope mounted (the one that comes on Barrett .50 "kits") which seems to hold up to the reverse recoil of the .50 just fine.  That said, a rifle of this caliber needs quality glass and I just don't feel like spending the money for a Nightforce or a Swarovski on a rifle that I barely shoot (I prefer to pack light).  If I shot match, it might be a different story, but since I don't, I'd rather have the cash and focus on my other precision rifles.  Note:  This is not the National Match edition, which has a tighter chamber and can have issues with military ammo (I hear).  Anyway, here is what you get:

- Rifle ($3,359)
- 15MOA scope base ($80)
- Bushnell 10X mildot ($200)
- Prince Bipod ($213)
- OD Green Pelican Case for the kit ($300)
- 10 rounds of Hornady A-MAX ($50)
Over $4,200 has been spent on this rifle.

I am open to trades: Savage 110B, Robinson XCR, PWS Diablo upper, SCAR, .300 Blackout SBR/Pistol upper, Aimpoint Micro, Aimpoint/Eotech 3X Multiplier, etc.  
As you can see, I'm only interested in quality products.  If you have something else you think I might like, let me know.  I am also looking to get a quality 60-80 gallon air compressor as well, so if you have one we can work it into the deal.

Obviously, I can pull the scope, as this is a "starter scope" for a rifle of this caliber.

I must say, this thing is insanely fun to shoot.  I have shot many .50BMG rifles, and the Armalite is by far the most enjoyable.

The RFB is not for sale, just for scale.

By responding to this post, you are stating you are of age, not a felon, and can legally own this weapon.

Let me know if you have any questions.  I will meet for serious inquiries only.

Henry rifle owners were inquiring when Henry would look back to our historical roots and their designers did just that. The result is the first American made .45 Colt Henry lever action featuring a solid brass receiver since the original Henry rifle of 1860.

The adventure and romance of America's Old West are imbedded in its distinctive 20" octagon barrel, straight-grip American walnut stock with brass buttplate and brass barrel band. The solid top brass receiver features side ejection. The overall length is 38½" and this powerhouse weighs in at 8.68 lbs.

A nice 19th century touch is the use of a fully adjustable Marble semi-buckhorn rear sight with white diamond insert and brass beaded front sight. The .45 Colt is the cartridge that was said to have "killed more game, big and small, and more men, good and bad, than any other in existence." Our tubular magazine can pack ten of these powerful bruisers. The .45 Colt is a serious hunting tool, and has proven itself time and time again on all of the world's game. We trust the Henry Big Boy .45 will soon become a favorite of big game hunters due to its handsome looks, rugged reliability and proven knockdown power.

The Henry Big Boy .45 Colt is also offered for you cowpokes who do Cowboy Action Shooting. The Big Boys have the smoothest actions of any centerfire lever action rifles on the market today. They work beautifully to give you competition shooters a leg up in any event you take part in.

Come visit Potestio Brothers Equipment in Parker for all of your  firearm needs. A large selection of varmint, big game and sporting  rifles kept on hand at all times, as well as  several grades and styles of shotguns to suit both hunting,  recreational trap and defense shooting.

Handguns including but not limited to Glock, Smith & Wesson, Springfield Armory, Ruger and Sig Sauer are among  our regularly stocked items.  From 1911’s to concealed carry, we have something in stock to meet your needs.
